make_plot <- function(.data) {
p <- .data %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x=price,y=clarity))+
  geom_point()+
  geom_point()

q <- plotly::ggplotly(p)
return(q)
}
  • make function that returns a plotly object
plot_tbl <- diamonds %>% 
  nest_by(cut) %>% 
  mutate(
    data=list(data)
    ,plots=
      trelliscopejs::map_plot(
        list(.x=data)
        ,.f=~make_plot(.data=.x))
      )
manipulateWidget::combineWidgets(ncol=2
                                 ,nrow=2
                                 ,plot_tbl$plots[[1]]
                                 ,plot_tbl$plots[[2]]
                                 ,plot_tbl$plots[[3]]
                                 ,plot_tbl$plots[[4]]
